-- Rusal Falls in Moscow as Aluminum Futures Decline in Shanghai
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-02-21T08:32:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/rusal-falls-in-moscow-as-aluminum-futures-decline-in-shanghai.html
United Co. Rusal, the world’s
largest aluminum producer, led declines in the Moscow-based
Micex Index as aluminum futures fell for a second day in
 Shanghai .  Rusal’s Russian depository receipts dropped 4.1 percent,
the biggest intraday decline since Dec. 16, to 247.41 rubles by
12:24 p.m. in Moscow. The stock has gained about 26 percent this
year.  Shares in the aluminum producer controlled by billionaire
 Oleg Deripaska  fell 4 percent today to HK$6.45 in in Hong Kong.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
